@hcolor@n command can be used to change text an background colors of the @hSHELL@n program.

@eSYNTAX:
@p$@n color @p[txtcolor@n,@pbgcolor@n,@pbordercolor]@n

Run the command without the arguments to view the current color values. You can run the command with arguments to change the colors. All 3 arguments have to be provided

@hNOTE:@n Command will @enot@n parse correctly if you put spaces after commas.@; Actually, you don't need to use commas - you can use spaces instead as a separator, or any kind of non-digit character.

@#r:color/palette